# Research Skills Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and configure as needed.
# Full MCP setup guide: guides/advanced/mcp-providers-setup.md

# ==========================================
# 1. MCP Provider Overrides (all optional)
# ==========================================
# Built-in providers (scholarly-search, citation-graph) work out of the box.
# The providers below are optional — configure them to enable richer evidence
# collection. Uncomment and fill in the command that starts each MCP server.
# See: guides/advanced/mcp-providers-setup.md for details on each provider.

# -- Literature search (override built-in Semantic Scholar) --
# Example: route to your local Zotero library instead
# RESEARCH_MCP_SCHOLARLY_SEARCH_CMD="npx -y @zcaceres/zotero-mcp-server"
# Optional: if you stay on the built-in Semantic Scholar provider, add an API key
# to reduce 429 rate-limit failures during repeated searches.
# SEMANTIC_SCHOLAR_API_KEY="your-semantic-scholar-key"

# Example: use a custom citation graph service
# RESEARCH_MCP_CITATION_GRAPH_CMD="python3 /path/to/your/custom_graph_mcp.py"

# -- Metadata normalization (DOI, author, journal enrichment) --
# Recommended: OpenAlex MCP  →  pip install openalex-mcp
# RESEARCH_MCP_METADATA_REGISTRY_CMD="python3 -m openalex_mcp"

# -- Full-text retrieval (PDF acquisition from local library or open access) --
# Recommended: Zotero MCP   →  npm install -g @zcaceres/zotero-mcp-server
# RESEARCH_MCP_FULLTEXT_RETRIEVAL_CMD="npx -y @zcaceres/zotero-mcp-server"

# -- Screening tracker (PRISMA inclusion/exclusion decision log) --
# Recommended: Rayyan MCP (see rayyan.ai developer docs) or a local stub
# RESEARCH_MCP_SCREENING_TRACKER_CMD="python3 /path/to/screening_mcp.py"

# -- Extraction store (structured data extracted from papers) --
# Recommended: Covidence MCP (see covidence.org) or a local CSV/SQLite stub
# RESEARCH_MCP_EXTRACTION_STORE_CMD="python3 /path/to/extraction_mcp.py"

# -- Stats engine (meta-analysis, mixed-effects models, Bayesian inference) --
# Recommended (R):      Rscript /path/to/stats_mcp.R
# Recommended (Python): python3 -m statsmodels_mcp   (custom script)
# RESEARCH_MCP_STATS_ENGINE_CMD="python3 /path/to/stats_mcp.py"

# -- Code runtime (sandboxed execution of generated research code) --
# Recommended: Jupyter MCP  →  pip install jupyter-mcp-server
# RESEARCH_MCP_CODE_RUNTIME_CMD="python3 -m jupyter_mcp_server"

# -- Reporting guidelines (CONSORT / PRISMA / STROBE / CHEERS checklist lookup) --
# Recommended: EQUATOR Network MCP (see equator-network.org) or a local stub
# RESEARCH_MCP_REPORTING_GUIDELINES_CMD="python3 /path/to/reporting_mcp.py"

# -- Submission kit (cover letter, CRediT statements, supplementary inventory) --
# Recommended: OJS MCP (see pkp.sfu.ca/ojs) or Overleaf MCP (experimental)
# RESEARCH_MCP_SUBMISSION_KIT_CMD="python3 /path/to/submission_mcp.py"

# ==========================================
# 1.5. Strict Literature Search Presets
# ==========================================
# Recommended "rigorous search" stack for review-grade academic work:
# 1) scholarly-search     → built-in Semantic Scholar, or your own multi-source MCP
# 2) metadata-registry    → OpenAlex MCP for DOI / author / venue normalization
# 3) citation-graph       → built-in citation graph, or a custom graph provider
# 4) fulltext-retrieval   → Zotero MCP / OA resolver for full text and provenance
#
# Example baseline:
# SEMANTIC_SCHOLAR_API_KEY="your-semantic-scholar-key"
# RESEARCH_MCP_METADATA_REGISTRY_CMD="python3 -m openalex_mcp"
#
# Example review-grade:
# RESEARCH_MCP_SCHOLARLY_SEARCH_CMD="python3 /path/to/multi_source_search_mcp.py"
# RESEARCH_MCP_METADATA_REGISTRY_CMD="python3 -m openalex_mcp"
# RESEARCH_MCP_CITATION_GRAPH_CMD="python3 /path/to/graph_mcp.py"
# RESEARCH_MCP_FULLTEXT_RETRIEVAL_CMD="npx -y @zcaceres/zotero-mcp-server"

# ==========================================
# 2. CLI UI Preferences
# ==========================================
# Set terminal output language (en or zh-CN)
RESEARCH_CLI_LANG="en"

# ==========================================
# 3. Model API Keys (If accessing directly via Orchestrator scripts)
# ==========================================
# OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-..."
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="sk-ant-..."
# GEMINI_API_KEY="AIza..."
